						<summary>

						<p>On a broken stone lying in the house near the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>1841 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated San. 1241. The reference might be to the Sūr-san, in which case it may be equated to 1841 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It seems to refer to the planting of trees. The inscription is written in Nāgarī characters and Marāṭhī language.</p>						

						</summary>
